@anchor{lsum}
@deffn {Function} lsum (@mvar{expr}, @mvar{x}, @mvar{L})

Represents the sum of @mvar{expr} for each element @mvar{x} in @mvar{L}.
A noun form @code{'lsum} is returned if the argument @mvar{L} does not evaluate
to a list.

Examples:

@c ===beg===
@c lsum (x^i, i, [1, 2, 7]);
@c lsum (i^2, i, rootsof (x^3 - 1));
@c ===end===
@example
(%i1) lsum (x^i, i, [1, 2, 7]);
                            7    2
(%o1)                      x  + x  + x
(%i2) lsum (i^2, i, rootsof (x^3 - 1));
@group
                     ====
                     \      2
(%o2)                 >    i
                     /
                     ====
                                   3
                     i in rootsof(x  - 1)
@end group
@end example

